        <num>CC 231</num>
        <heading>231.  Parents' obligation to deliver and account</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 231.  Parents' obligation to deliver and account
Parents are bound to deliver to the child his property at termination of parental
authority.
Parents shall also give an account of their administration when ordered by the court. 
The action to compel an accounting is subject to a liberative prescription of five years that
commences to run from the day the child attains the age of majority.</p>
        </content>
